Now, let's evaluate $f(r) + f(s) + f(t)$:

\begin{align*}
f(r) + f(s) + f(t) &= 4r^3 - 59r^2 + 4s^3 - 59s^2 + 4t^3 - 59t^2 \\
&= 4(r^3 + s^3 + t^3) - 59(r^2 + s^2 + t^2).
\end{align*}

We can use the identity $r^3 + s^3 + t^3 - 3rst = (r + s + t)(r^2 + s^2 + t^2 - rs - rt - st)$.  We know $r + s + t = 59/4$, so

\begin{align*}
r^3 + s^3 + t^3 &= 3rst + (r + s + t)(r^2 + s^2 + t^2 - rs - rt - st) \\
&= 3rst + \frac{59}{4}(r^2 + s^2 + t^2 - rs - rt - st).
\end{align*}

Again by Vieta's formulas, $rst = -32/4 = -8$.  Also,

\begin{align*}
r^2 + s^2 + t^2 &= (r + s + t)^2 - 2(rs + rt + st) \\
